```python
def find_outlier(integers):
    '''
    count number of even integers in integers[:3]
    if there are more than 1 even integers, find the odd integer
    else find the even integer
    '''
    temp = 0
    count = sum([temp+1 for i in integers[:3] if i%2 == 0])  
    if count > 1: 
        outlier = next(x for x in integers if x % 2 == 1 )    
    else:
        outlier = next(x for x in integers if x % 2 == 0 )
    return outlier
```
